The paper deals with spatial search strategies for open government data, which involves information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) techniques. The use of metadata enhancement and user-based evaluation also suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (HC) and cybernetics (CY). Additionally, the development of a prototype and theoretical evaluation may involve aspects of digital libraries (DL).
